quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
  27,64,"Or who<i class=""s"">(else then) </i>is the one who originates creation and then restores it, and Who provides for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>from the sky and the land? Is there any other god with Allah? Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Produce your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>proof, if you are truthful.”"
  27,65,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “No one in the heavens or the earth knows what is hidden except Allah.” For they are unaware of when they will be resurrected;"
  27,66,"rather, <span class=""h"">their knowledge has been reached<sup foot_note=""80751"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>in the Hereafter; rather, they are in doubt about it; rather, they are completely blind to it."
  27,67,"And those who denied said, “<span class=""h"">Can it be that<sup foot_note=""80752"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>when we have become dust, and our forefathers—<span class=""h"">can it be that</span>we will really be brought out?"
  27,68,"Most surely, we were promised this before, we and our forefathers; this is nothing but the legends of the ancients.”"
  27,69,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Journey through the earth and look what the outcome was for the criminals.”"
  27,70,"But do<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not grieve over them and do not be troubled by what they scheme."
  27,71,"And they say, “When is this promise, if you are truthful?”"
  27,72,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Perhaps some of what you are asking to be hastened has drawn near.”"
  27,73,"And indeed, your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord is surely the Possessor of grace towards mankind, but most of them are not thankful."
  27,74,"And indeed, your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord knows whatever their chests harbor and whatever they make public."
  27,75,"And never is there anything hidden in the heaven or the earth but it is in an evident record{1}.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘scripture’.
  27,76,"This Recital{1}indeed narrates to the Children of Israel most of what they differ over,",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
